## Feature: Append-mode Ontology Import with Conflict Detection

### Context
Importing an OWL or RDFS file previously erased the entire ontology (full list replacement via `dict.update()`). Users needed a way to merge multiple ontology files without losing existing work. This feature introduces an append-mode import that first detects conflicts, presents them to the user for resolution, and only then merges the new entities into the current session.

### Changes

1. **`src/back/core/w3c/owl/OntologyConflictDetector.py`** (new) — `OntologyConflictDetector` class with `analyze(existing, incoming)` returning a JSON-serialisable `ConflictReport`. Classifies each incoming entity as `new`, `duplicate`, `uri_conflict`, or `name_conflict` across classes, properties, constraints, SWRL rules, groups, axioms, and expressions.

2. **`src/back/core/w3c/owl/__init__.py`** — exports `OntologyConflictDetector`, `ConflictReport`, `ConflictItem`.

3. **`src/back/objects/ontology/Ontology.py`** — added three methods:
   - `analyze_import(content, format)` — parse-and-diff, read-only, no session mutation.
   - `merge_parsed_owl_to_domain(content, resolutions, format)` — append-mode merge with per-entity resolution (skip / overwrite / rename).
   - `_apply_resolutions(entity_type, existing, report, resolutions)` — static merge helper.

4. **`src/api/routers/internal/ontology.py`** — two new routes:
   - `POST /ontology/analyze-import` — read-only conflict analysis.
   - `POST /ontology/merge-import` — append merge accepting `resolutions` map.

5. **`src/shared/fastapi/main.py`** — added `/analyze-import` to `_STATUS_GATE_OPEN_SUFFIXES` (non-mutating, bypass version lock check).

6. **`src/front/templates/partials/ontology/_ontology_import.html`** — OWL and RDFS panes now have a Replace / Append radio selector and a conflict-resolution panel (summary badges, conflict table with per-row resolution dropdown, Confirm & Append button).

7. **`src/front/static/ontology/js/ontology-import.js`** — rewritten OWL and RDFS handlers to support the two-phase flow; FIBO/CDISC/IOF/FHIR handlers unchanged.

### Modified Files
- `src/back/core/w3c/owl/OntologyConflictDetector.py` (new)
- `src/back/core/w3c/owl/__init__.py`
- `src/back/objects/ontology/Ontology.py`
- `src/api/routers/internal/ontology.py`
- `src/shared/fastapi/main.py`
- `src/front/templates/partials/ontology/_ontology_import.html`
- `src/front/static/ontology/js/ontology-import.js`
- `tests/units/ontology/test_conflict_detector.py` (new)

