## Fix: SKOS Vocabulary Import Support

### Context
SKOS taxonomy files (`.ttl`) using `skos:Concept` / `skos:prefLabel` / `skos:broader` were silently producing an empty ontology on import because neither the OWL parser nor the RDFS parser handled SKOS triples. Files like `classification.ttl` (RATP asset taxonomy) could be selected via the file picker (`.ttl` is an accepted extension) but yielded zero classes after parsing.

### Changes

1. **`src/back/core/w3c/rdfs/RDFSParser.py`**
   - Added `SKOS` namespace constant (`http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#`).
   - `get_classes()` — also iterates `skos:Concept` instances in addition to `rdfs:Class` / `owl:Class`.
   - `_extract_class_info()` — falls back to `skos:prefLabel` when no `rdfs:label` is found; falls back to `skos:definition` for description; resolves `skos:broader` (with label lookup) as the parent when no `rdfs:subClassOf` is present.
   - `get_ontology_info()` — detects `skos:ConceptScheme` (with `rdfs:label` / `skos:prefLabel`) as the vocabulary root, before falling back to base-URI heuristics.

2. **`src/back/objects/ontology/Ontology.py`**
   - `analyze_import()` (RDFS branch) — raises `ValidationError` with a descriptive message when zero classes and zero properties are found after parsing, instead of silently returning an empty conflict report.
   - `_merge_rdfs()` — same guard: raises `ValidationError` with supported-format hints if the parser finds nothing.

### Modified Files
- `src/back/core/w3c/rdfs/RDFSParser.py`
- `src/back/objects/ontology/Ontology.py`

### Test Results
- 428 passed, 11 skipped — full suite green.

