## Fix: Alignment/Mapping File Import Support

### Context
Alignment files like `alignments-era.ttl` use no explicit class type declarations (`rdfs:Class`, `owl:Class`, `skos:Concept`). They define cross-ontology mappings via SKOS alignment predicates (`skos:exactMatch`, `skos:closeMatch`, etc.) and OWL assertions (`owl:equivalentClass`, `owl:differentFrom`). Resources are identified only by `rdfs:label`. Previous parser found 0 classes and 0 properties.

### Changes

1. **`src/back/core/w3c/rdfs/RDFSParser.py`**
   - `get_classes()` — adds labeled-resources fallback: when no typed classes are found, collects all subjects of `rdfs:label` that are named URIs outside standard W3C/SKOS namespaces. Produces the ERA/RATP external entities as importable classes.
   - `get_properties()` — adds SKOS alignment property extraction: when `skos:exactMatch`, `skos:closeMatch`, `skos:broadMatch`, `skos:narrowMatch`, `skos:relatedMatch`, `owl:equivalentClass`, or `owl:differentFrom` predicates are actually used in the graph, they are added as `ObjectProperty` entries.

### Modified Files
- `src/back/core/w3c/rdfs/RDFSParser.py`

### Test Results
- 428 passed, 11 skipped — full suite green.
- `alignments-era.ttl`: 29 classes (ERA + RATP-SKOS labeled entities), 7 alignment ObjectProperties.

---

## Fix: SHACL Shapes File Import Support

### Context
SHACL files like `shapes.ttl` define validation constraints using `sh:NodeShape` + `sh:targetClass`. No explicit `rdfs:Class`, `owl:Class`, or `skos:Concept` declarations → parsers returned empty results.

### Changes

1. **`src/back/core/w3c/rdfs/RDFSParser.py`**
   - Added `SH` namespace constant (`http://www.w3.org/ns/shacl#`).
   - `get_classes()` — extracts `sh:targetClass` values from every `sh:NodeShape` as importable classes.
   - `get_properties()` — extracts property names from `sh:property` URI local segments (`{base}#{ClassName}Shape/{propName}`) as deduplicated `DatatypeProperty` entries, with `domain` set to the owning class.

