## Feature: Entity search popup in Ontology Designer

### Context
Added a search button (🔍) to the Ontology Designer toolbar. Clicking it opens a small floating popup with a sorted dropdown of all entities. Selecting one and clicking "Focus" centres the canvas on that entity (animated pan+zoom to ×1.4) and triggers the neighbourhood highlight — identical to clicking the node directly.

### Changes

1. **`src/front/templates/partials/ontology/_ontology_map.html`**
   - Added `#mapSearchBtn` toolbar button and `#mapSearchPopup` floating panel (select + Focus button).

2. **`src/front/static/ontology/css/ontology-map.css`**
   - Added `.map-search-popup`, `.map-search-popup-header`, `.map-search-popup-body` styles with fade-in animation.

3. **`src/front/static/ontology/js/ontology-map.js`**
   - `initMapSearch(nodes, highlightNeighborhood, clearHighlights, svg, w, h)` — wires open/close, populates the sorted dropdown on each open, handles Enter key, outside-click dismiss.
   - `focusMapEntity(name, nodes, …)` — pans and zooms the SVG to centre the selected node, then calls `highlightNeighborhood`.
   - `initOntologyMap` now calls `initMapSearch` at the end of its setup block.

